#week-title("Two", "Acid & Alkali in the Laboratory")

=== Core Teaching

The philosophical understanding of Acid and Alkali reflects deeper cosmic
principles. In the laboratory, we see these expressed as pH levels and chemical
reactivity.

The alchemist moves between these poles deliberately. By using an acid medium,
we can dissolve (volatilise) a fixed mineral. By using an alkaline salt, we can
attract and capture (fix) a volatile spirit. Learning to balance these reactions
is a core skill of Year Two.

=== Topics This Week

- Philosophical understanding of pH in alchemical work
- Fixing the volatile and volatilising the fixed
- The "Middle" medium: why nothing passes directly from one extreme to another

#inner-work[
  *The Polar Tension*

  Contemplate the polar tension in your own nature this week.
  - What in you tends toward *volatility* (dispersion, movement, inspiration)?
  - What in you tends toward *fixity* (habit, solidity, endurance)?

  Identify the "medium" or "middle" in your character that allows you to
  balance these two extremes. Record your findings in your journal.
]

